main event: Four brightly illuminated, diamond-shaped objects traveled in formation over Kent, England on October 27, 1955.
interesting points: The objects were accompanied by a radar return.
The objects were estimated to be at an altitude of 800 - 1,000 feet.
Several civilian crews of vessels at sea off the northeast coast of Kent also reported seeing a similar object around the same time.
The object was described as a brilliant light that appeared to hang in the air, move erratically, and then disappear from view, indicating it was not a conventional aircraft.
witnesses: RAF intelligence officer, civilian crews at sea
